  "motivation": "The current Gamepad API relies on a polling-based model, where applications must repeatedly call navigator.getGamepads() and compare the entire gamepad state to detect changes such as button presses or axis movements. Introducing an event-driven alternative would allow applications to respond directly to meaningful input changes without relying on a polling loop. This approach not only simplifies input handling but may also help reduce average input latency.",
